header: ['Volkswagen invests extra $200 million in U.S. battery company QuantumScape']
article content: ['BERLIN (Reuters) - Volkswagen is increasing its stake in U.S. company QuantumScape by up to $200 million to boost the development of solid-state battery technology that aims to increase the ranges of electric cars and shorten charging times, the German carmaker said ', ' on Tuesday. ', 'Volkswagen added that plans for a pilot plant were expected to be firmed up in the course of this year. ', 'Reporting by Thomas Seythal; Editing by Michelle Martin']

header: ['Former Volkswagen employee sought by U.S. arrested in Croatia: Handelsblatt']
article content: ['FRANKFURT (Reuters) - Axel Eiser, a former Volkswagen (', ') engineer being sought by United States authorities as part of their investigation into a diesel-emissions cheating scandal, has been arrested in Croatia, Germany’s Handelsblatt said on Tuesday. ', 'Eiser is a former head of group powertrain development at Volkswagen and was also a director of powertrain development at VW’s premium brand Audi (', ').  ', 'In January 2019 a federal grand jury in Detroit indicted former Audi managers as part of the U.S. government’s investigation into diesel emissions cheating. ', 'VW admitted in September 2015 to secretly installing software to cheat anti-pollution tests, triggering a global backlash against combustion-engined vehicles. ', 'Volkswagen and Audi declined to comment. ', 'Reporting by Jan Schwartz; Writing by Edward Taylor; Editing by Thomas Escritt']

header: ['Volkswagen to pay $267 million for Audi buyout']
article content: ['FRANKFURT (Reuters) - Volkswagen (', ') will pay a 48% premium to buy out the minority shareholders of premium division Audi (', '), Audi said on Tuesday. ', 'Volkswagen, which already holds 99.64% of Audi, announced the squeeze-out plans in February. ', '“Volkswagen AG announced and specified that it has set the cash settlement to be paid to the minority shareholders in return for the transfer of their shares at 1,551.53 euros per AUDI AG share,” the carmaker said. ', 'This compares with a share price of 1,050 euros apiece on Tuesday and amounts to a purchase price of 237 million euros ($267 million) for the 152,749 outstanding Audi shares, according to Refinitiv data. ', 'The transfer will be passed at Audi’s next annual general meeting, which the carmaker said is expected to take place in July or August. ', 'Reporting by Christoph Steitz; editing by David Evans']
